<br>
Quick question, have you played another class and fought againts a mage before? This is why I ask....<br>
<br>
When I started on Tallon Zek with my Mage, I started to get very disapointed once I got to the 20's range I appeared to be doing something wrong because I couldn't win a dem fight.<br>
<br>
I then created a warrior, wizard, bard, sk, and cleric within that time. Each had encountered a mage and there was 1 major thing I really learned from those encounters. The pet controlled the tempo of the battle. If it was on me continously it would spell disaster. With those classes I figured out every possible way to disable the pet so I could concentrate on the mage.<br>
<br>
Well, picking my mage back up I started to use my pet more for the fear factor rather than the damage factor. I learned that people, like me, tended to freak out and not perform up to par when that pet was constantly beating away. I took a look at my tactics in disabling a mages pet and figured out how I could prevent them from happening to my mage. <br>
<br>
By keeping the pet on the opponant, at all times, it gives me more control over the battle. Each failed attempt to disable my pet by my opponant is more time for me to analyse the battle and do as I wish.   <br>
<br>
Heading off topic... <br>
<br>
Druids: There is the cheap way to gaurantee a successful kill. Go in unbuffed (earth pet, unbuffed). <br>
<br>
1.)Spam cancel/anul magic on him to disable his buffs (sow, bye bye!).<br>
2.) Send in pet.<br>
3.) Spam lvl 8 dd.<br>
** Cancel/Anul any DOTS/snares on you or your pet. This is the lowest of all tactics, but hey. You will win **<br>
<br>
Rangers: Depending on how twinked the Ranger is and how lucky he gets, I can take them out maybe 60% of the time. You can either go Earth pet and hope for a succeful Root, then follow up with continous Mal's until 1 sticks, then DD till the cows come home. Or go fire and reverse kite (cancel/anul and snares on you FAST!).<br>
<br>
I should announce again, my experince is only from lvls 1-34, however I know many High Level mages on Tallon Zek who will vouch for me that keeping the pet on your opponant at all times is key to a glorious victory!<br>
<br>
<br>
